ne omnia—ad primas notiones. The πρόληψις which arises instinct- ively from the repeated appearances of Gods is contrasted with the ab- straet reasonings which follow. The Gods must be of human shape, for the most perfect nature must be also the most beautiful, and the human shape is more beautiful than any other3 again, happiness cannot exist without virtue, nor virtue without reason, nor reason except in human shape.
